                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 <persName corresp="#p_WRACH1"
                        >Woodward</persName> Electoral Mission/98a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HME1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-23T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 23, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. Personal for <persName corresp="#p_WRACH1">Admiral Woodward</persName> from
                    the Secretary. I want you to know that we appreciate the difficulties which you
                    may have to face in carrying out the supervision with a possibly reduced and
                    less selective personnel. We made every effort we could to see that you were
                    furnished with the full complement of personnel contemplated by the plan for
                    electoral supervision discussed with you on your last visit to the Department,
                    but circumstances beyond our control have made this impossible. However, I have
                    every confidence that you are going to do an admirable piece of work and give
                    the Nicaraguans a highly satisfactory supervision. You may be assured that we
                    are doing and shall do everything we can to give you full support.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
